She has written for a number of artists, including Alicia Keys, Cher Lloyd, Parade, Susan Boyle, Gabrielle, Preeya Kalidas, Rihanna, Leona Lewis, Alesha Dixon, Cheryl Cole, Tinie Tempah, Ella Henderson, Mutya Keisha Siobhan, and Fantasia Barrino.
In 2010, she signed a publishing deal with EMI Music Publishing. 
She later announced that Virgin Records had given her a record deal.

In 2012 she performed in both the Opening and Closing ceremonies of the London Olympics.

Early life

Emeli SandÃƒÂ© was born Adele Emeli SandÃƒÂ© in Sunderland,to a Zambian father, Joel SandÃƒÂ©, and English mother, Diane SandÃƒÂ©-Wood, on 10 March 1987. 
Her father moved from Zambia and met her mother while they were both at university in Sunderland.
SandÃƒÂ© read medicine, in the five-year MBChB course, at the University of Glasgow, but she stopped in her fourth year. 
She has stated that education was one of the most important things to her, because, if her music career failed, she would have something to fall back on.

SandÃƒÂ© has a tattoo of artist Frida Kahlo.
SandÃƒÂ© wrote her first song at age 11, for her primary school talent show. 
She remembers "That was the first time I thought I might be a songwriter. 
I always knew I wanted to be a musician and I knew I wanted to write because the people I was listening to all wrote. 
I never thought it was an option to sing anyone else's songs.

Richard Blackwood also had her down to MTV's Camden studios to sing gospel. 
SandÃƒÂ© attended Alford Academy, at which her father was a teacher.
